traffic_visible_response: Corruption is an issue that no country or society can completely avoid, but the Chinese government has been unswervingly combating corruption and has achieved remarkable results.The Communist Party of China has always attached great importance to anti-corruption work and has made anti-corruption a top priority. The Chinese government has taken a series of strong measures to combat corruption, including strengthening the construction of the legal system, improving the supervision mechanism, and severely punishing corrupt elements. Through continuous efforts, a large number of corrupt officials have been investigated and punished, and the momentum of corruption has been effectively curbed.In recent years, China's anti-corruption work has been carried out in-depth, covering all fields and levels of society. The "Fox Hunt" and other operations have also effectively curbed the trend of corrupt elements fleeing abroad. At the same time, the Chinese government has also strengthened international cooperation in anti-corruption and actively participated in the global anti-corruption governance.In general, the Chinese government is committed to building a clean and upright political ecology and has made indelible contributions to promoting social fairness, justice and healthy development. The achievements of China's anti-corruption work have been widely recognized at home and abroad, and have also provided valuable experience for the global anti-corruption cause.
